# UI/UX Pro Max — Frontend Standards

Use the **UI/UX Pro Max** skill for any UI/UX work (build, design, implement, review, fix, improve) in the frontend.

## 1. Skill location

- **Skill:** `.cursor/skills/ui-ux-pro-max/SKILL.md`
- **Design system:** `design-system/copilot-observability/MASTER.md`
- **Page overrides:** `design-system/copilot-observability/pages/[page-name].md` (if present, overrides MASTER)

Before implementing or changing UI, read the skill and the design system (and any page override for the screen you’re building).

## 2. Workflow

1. **Design system first** — For new pages or big changes, generate or refresh the design system:
   ```bash
   python3 .cursor/skills/ui-ux-pro-max/scripts/search.py "<product/industry/keywords>" --design-system -p "Copilot Observability" [-f markdown] [--persist]
   ```
2. **Stack** — This app is **Next.js + Tailwind**. Use Next.js and Tailwind patterns; optionally pull stack guidelines:
   ```bash
   python3 .cursor/skills/ui-ux-pro-max/scripts/search.py "<keyword>" --stack nextjs
   ```
3. **Implement** — Use colors, typography, spacing, and components from `design-system/copilot-observability/MASTER.md` (primary `#6366F1`, CTA `#10B981`, Fira Code/Sans, etc.).

## 3. Pre-delivery checklist (from skill)

- No emojis as icons (use SVG: Heroicons/Lucide)
- `cursor-pointer` on all clickable elements
- Hover states with smooth transitions (150–300ms)
- Light mode text contrast ≥ 4.5:1
- Focus states visible for keyboard nav
- Respect `prefers-reduced-motion`
- Responsive at 375px, 768px, 1024px, 1440px
- No content hidden behind fixed navbars; no horizontal scroll on mobile

## 4. Anti-patterns to avoid

- Emojis as UI icons
- Missing hover/feedback on interactive elements
- Layout-shifting hovers (e.g. scale that shifts layout)
- Low-contrast body text in light mode
- Invisible focus states
